Violent protests shut down the Durban University of Technology with three campuses closing their doors. Operations were suspended on Tuesday. Four vehicles were torched during the protests. Alan Khan, Senior Director of Corporate Affairs at the Durban University of Technology, spoke with eNCA's Dan Moyane about the situation. Courtesy of #DStv403 DURBAN - The Durban University of Technology says violent protests have caused serious damage to its campuses. A security guard is said to have suffered head injuries while trying to quell tensions. WATCH:Â DUT protests | University temporarily suspends operations Students have complained about difficulties registering. Three campuses are now temporarily closed. The university says this is to ensure the safety of its staff.